import nltk
nltk.download('punkt')
from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize

def find_given_names(name, sentence):
    given_names = []
    words = word_tokenize(sentence)
    for word in words:
        if word.lower() == name.lower():
            index = words.index(word)
            if index > 0 and (words[index-1].isalpha() and words[index-1][-1] == ','):
                given_names.append(word.lower())
    return ';'.join(given_names)

# Test the function
print(find_given_names("Haydn", "but, after all, why not have given a symphony or overture of Haydn or Mozart?"))

import re

def extract_given_names(person):
    # Regular expression pattern to match given names, which are sequences of one or more
    # uppercase or titlecase letters followed by a period or space.
    pattern = r'[A-Za-z.]+'

    given_names = '; '.join(re.findall(pattern, person))
